en_question:
    The distances between 4 cities are given in Table 7-24. Find the shortest path and total distance starting from city v_1, visiting all other cities exactly once, and finally returning to v_1. Solve the problem using dynamic programming.

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Distance matrix between cities (Table 7-24)}
    \renewcommand{\arraystretch}{1.2}
    \begin{tabular}{c|cccc}
        \toprule
        Distance $d(v_i, v_j)$ & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\
        \midrule
        1 & 0 & 6 & 7 & 9 \\
        2 & 8 & 0 & 9 & 7 \\
        3 & 5 & 8 & 0 & 8 \\
        4 & 6 & 5 & 5 & 0 \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}

cn_question:
